sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Chimera Pr
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Probe coding for alpha fragment of beta gal
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The following part consists of a constitutive promoter plus RBS (BBa_J61100), which codes for the protein Streptavidin linked to the alpha fragment of Beta Galactosidase via Linker (BBa_J176040).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Abhinav Markus
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Working unit constructed using parts in the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part works only with its omega compliment. But can also be expressed if transformed in cells that code for the omega fragment of Beta Galactosidase.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PLflex
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Flexible linker peptide made of two GGGGS repeats
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Karmella Haynes

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for streptavidin which binds with biotin. The streptavidin coding region does not contain any rbs nor terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shi Lei

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lacZ-alpha
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: In strains with lacZ-omega (lacZ N-terminal deletion mutant) like DH5alpha, DH10B and Top10, lacZ-alpha restores the beta-galactosidase activity.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhan Jian
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: PCR amplified from BBa_J33202 without the RBS.
